OL,6,FWhile the commission noted that
OL,7,Fsupplying a binder to a young person
OL,8,Fis not a criminal offence, it found a
OL,9,F"lack of transparency" on at least two
OL,10,Foccasions, where the charity told
OL,11,Fsomeone inquiring about a binder that
OL,12,Fthey did not have the right size in
OL,13,Fstock, rather than informing them they
OL,14,Fhad failed the organisation's checks.
